s. It seems like the test's message class should be in the child loader, but the existing structure complicates things, especially if I want to define a separate source package for tests!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating classloading issues**\\n\\nI'm looking into a custom classloader for native images, specifically for loading classes from the classpath after a build. It seems like it might not be supported, so I need to catch an UnsupportedFeatureError. In the JVM, the agent collects errors, but in a native context, I'll need to catch and assert the error myself. I'll also check if NativeImageSupport is imported and whether this dependency is available with the TCK. Now, it’s time to search!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_WgjnJ99ogCGOc8qJlkim4HuB|fc_05d42684ccbfc26e016a0f5fa2d5d481938189f90e4087de62", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"NativeImageSupport\" tests/src/org.apache.kafka tests/src | head -20"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1465, "output": 1006, "cacheRead": 39936, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 42407, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1779392400284, "responseId": "resp_05d42684ccbfc26e016a0f5f90ea208193a8f42186f003659c"}}
